Okay, ab technical explanation lo jisme thoda dimaag hil jaye:
In Kubernetes, Liveness and Readiness probes are configured in the PodSpec to periodically check the containerâ€™s state.
Liveness determines whether the container is running or dead â€” failure triggers a restart.
Readiness checks if the application is ready to receive traffic.
They can use exec, httpGet, or tcpSocket actions, and rely on response codes to update pod status in kubelet, affecting the endpoints in the service load balancer. ğŸ˜µâ€ğŸ’«

